## Design Problem Statement

* **Problem:**   
  	Sharing address / privacy / safety  
  	Shame in accepting donations  
  	Lack of awareness of free donations  
  	Wasting products that can be repurposed

* **Users:**   
  	Women  
  	Those who want to remain anonymous accepting / donating  
  	Thrifters / refurbishers  
  	Those in need  
  	Charities

* **Activities:**   
  	Reusing items  
  	Contribute to greener environment  
  	Save money  
  	Donating  
  	  
* **What exists currently?**  
  	Currently people donate to churches or physical locations (Goodwill) or just throw away items. Another way is to join facebook groups that donate items in your area. It can be unsafe to hand out your address to strangers on the internet, or have your profile associated with giving / receiving free items. 

* **Essential functions:**   
  	Anonymous interaction/ user verification, in app scheduling for pickup,	Labeling items properly, filtering searches by location, label, condition. Receiving confirmation for pick up / accuracy of location / accuracy of items posted. 

## Focused Competitive Analysis

![][image1]

**Goodwill** is a method of donating, but takes your donated items and sells them back for profit. This is a convenient way to donate if you just want to take the items somewhere and drop them off. Although those items are getting to be reused instead of ending up in a landfill, it would be better to donate them to those in need directly. A con of Goodwill is the need for human interaction in order to donate.  
**Craigslist** is a website that has an overwhelming amount of links to click. A pro is you can search by location, and get specific with what you are searching for based on provided categories and a search bar.  A con is that there are many scams, so it’s now known as untrustworthy. Another notable pro to craigslist is that it doesn’t share personal email addresses, but creates an encrypted email. 

**Facebook Marketplace** is typically a site used for buying and selling items, but oftentimes items are listed with “FREE” in their description.  The site allows users to use a search function, but can only filter items based on set categories the item must be listed as.  A pro is the ability to search by location, search by item name, and that each item requires at least one photo to list.  Cons include manually scheduling meetings for pickup over instant messaging, lack of filtering options, and the access to personal social media profiles through the listing.
